kground_parallax=\"none\" enable_mobile=\"no\" parallax_speed=\"0.3\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" background_position=\"left top\" video_url=\"\" video_aspect_ratio=\"16:9\" video_webm=\"\" video_mp4=\"\" video_ogv=\"\" video_preview_image=\"\" overlay_color=\"\" overlay_opacity=\"0.5\" video_mute=\"yes\" video_loop=\"yes\" fade=\"no\" border_size=\"0px\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"\" padding_top=\"20\" padding_bottom=\"20\" padding_left=\"\" padding_right=\"\" hundred_percent=\"no\" equal_height_columns=\"no\" hide_on_mobile=\"no\" menu_anchor=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][fusion_text]\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"c4\">The WW2100 simulation tools use the Envision modeling framework to simulate natural and human processes at daily and annual timesteps from 2010 through 2099. Processes include streamflow, evapotransporation, forest growth and harvest, wildfire, agricultural production, irrigation, urban growth, reservoir operation, municipal water use and water rights.  </span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"c4\">For more information about WW2100, go to </span><span class=\"c9 c4 c14\"><a class=\"c10\" href=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=http://water.oregonstate.edu/ww2100&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1460746316728000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHcuZimIvk5kaIEVg_MGoURZLh2zg\">http://water.oregonstate.edu/ww2100</a></span><span class=\"c4\">.</span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Freshwater combines the talents of David water and ecological modeling expertise,  with Brian\' s Geographic Information Systems (GIS), web/mobile mapping and Remote Sensing skill set. Brian Fulfrost started the firm. in 2011 after working for nearly 20 years developing robust and innovative GIS applications in government, the private sector, and academia. The firm\'s focus is on utilizing geospatial technologies to assist in improved decision making in sustainable land use planning, active transportation (walkability/bikeability) as well as in natural resource management, environmental regulation, and conservation, and climate change adaptation. Our technical services include data collection (using sub meter GPS or imagery sources), database and application development, spatial data modeling, and cartographic visualization. Our mapping products are designed to use the most effective platforms for flexibility, scalability, and ease of use. The firm is committed to bridging the gap between the appropriate mapping technology and our client\'s specific needs – catering our solutions to produce  seamless GIS solutions. Our clients include local, state and federal government agencies and non-profits. The experience and insights that we have acquired over many years in the GIS industry allow us to offer our clients the most efficient and effective mapping solutions.</span></h3>\r\n[/fusion_text][/fullwidth][fullwidth background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_parallax=\"none\" enable_mobile=\"no\" parallax_speed=\"0.3\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" background_position=\"left top\" video_url=\"\" video_aspect_ratio=\"16:9\" video_webm=\"\" video_mp4=\"\" video_ogv=\"\" video_preview_image=\"\" overlay_color=\"\" overlay_opacity=\"0.5\" video_mute=\"yes\" video_loop=\"yes\" fade=\"no\" border_size=\"0px\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"\" padding_top=\"20\" padding_bottom=\"20\" padding_left=\"\" padding_right=\"\" hundred_percent=\"no\" equal_height_columns=\"no\" hide_on_mobile=\"no\" menu_anchor=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"][fusion_text]\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Service Areas</h1>\r\n[/fusion_text][one_third last=\"no\" spacing=\"yes\" center_content=\"no\" hide_on_mobile=\"no\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" background_position=\"left top\" hover_type=\"none\" link=\"\" border_position=\"all\" border_size=\"0px\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"\" padding=\"\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" animation_type=\"\" animat